description:
- Possibility to pass parameters to macros
- New AutoMacro macro with better customizability
- Nodes are marked as script nodes when arising from script execution. For macros, auto etc: Only the first nodes. Marking script nodes with new symbol in proof tree view.
- Fixed (a little hackish) the cancel button in the ProofScriptWorker: Now interface does not get stuck any more.
- Fixed selection of first open goal after first subtree of previously chosen goal has been closed
- Added "matches" parameter for rule and macro: RegEx-Matching of parts of a sequent formula, which is way more convenient than putting the whole formula into the script (sometimes currently also the only way because of problems when parsing non-trivial Java blocks)
- Added saveInst/saveNewName commands for putting the instantiation of a previous rule application into the AbbrevMap
- Added simple echo command for feedback to human users
- Increased size of proof script worker window such that it always fits its input (which is truncated to a maximum size)

I did all this to make the following proof script, producing a proof of 100,000 nodes, work. Maybe it's the most complicated one ever produced, I don't know... Doesn't run on the master because based on two experimental technologies: Abstract Execution, and a new loop (scope) invariant *taclet*.

